==German==

===Etymology===
Old High German ''[[strazza]]'', originally *''stratta'', from Late Latin ''[[strata]]''. Compare Dutch ''[[straat]]''
===Pronunciation===
shtra:së
===Noun===
'''Straße''' ''f'' (pl. ''Straßen'')

# a paved [[road]], especially in the city
# [[street]]
# [[carriageway]], the part of the road used by vehicles
# [[strait]]

===Usage===
* ''Die '''Straße''' ist [[breit]].'' (The street is wide.)
* ''Das Kind überquerte die '''Straße''''' (The child crossed the road)

